USD 429 Troy was informed by the Doniphan County Health Department of a positive COVID-19 case of a Troy High School Student. We are currently working with the Health Department to do contact tracing. The Health Dept. will contact the families of the students that may have been in close contact with the student. The school district will continue to update parents & students on this situation as we communicate with the Heath Dept.
PreK-6 will be in session on Tues., Sept. 1. Buses will run.
GRADES 7-12 WILL NOT BE IN SESSION ON TUES., SEPTEMBER 1ST. NO ACTIVITIES WILL TAKE PLACE ON TUES., SEPTEMBER 1ST. THE VOLLEYBALL QUAD FOR THS STUDENTS @ ONAGA IS CANCELLED.
VOCATIONAL STUDENTS ARE NOT TO ATTEND VOCATIONAL CLASSES ON TUES., SEPTEMBER 1ST.
Please check the school website (www.troyusd.org) as more updates will be posted as they become available.

post_text:
Trojan Fans! We have some exciting news! Here is a chance to not miss any of the action this season!

Twin Valley League COVID Guidelines: The Twin Valley League will require face masks at all indoor events. Masks are strongly recommended at outside events. At some indoor activities, fans will be limited or not allowed at all. Tournaments for Volleyball could also be limited access for fans. Temperatures may be taken at some schools before entering for games. Please follow the school district on our website at www.troyusd.org or one of our Facebook pages Troy Grade School/Troy High School/Troy Public Schools No. 429 or on twitter @TroyTrojans429. The district will update weekly on the limited attendance, temp. checks, or cancellation of games. Thank you for your patience and your cooperation as we work through this time. We hope adding the NFHS Cameras and Live game coverage will help fans be able to follow the Trojans!

2020-2021 Troy Dance Team
Tryout Information

Coach: Kristi Hensley-I will be teaching 5th & 6th grade Writing and Language at Troy Grade School this school year. I am excited to be your coach this year and I look forward to an exciting and fun year.

Tryouts: Tuesday, August 18th
Time: : 6:00 PM
Location: C. W. Oliver Gym

Requirements: Practice and learn the dance in the video provided to the best of your ability.

I know you may not own poms that is not a problem, just practice using a fist.

If there are dance moves you are unfamiliar with please do not let that keep you from trying out.

I want to see your abilities. This will help me choreograph our dances.

Video Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dGl7Tzl1Cmw&t=2s
Video credit: Elizabeth Thomas; Fayetteville HS

KSHSAA Physical Forms
To be eligible for participation in interscholastic athletics/spirit groups, a student in upcoming grades 7-12 must have on file with the school district a signed physical form before the first day of practices start on August 17th! The annual history and the physical examination shall not be taken earlier than May 1 preceding the school year for which it is applicable. post_text:
We know this has been a crazy spring for all! The district is still making plans for the 2020-21 school year. KSHSAA has released the NEW KSHSAA Physical Forms for the 2020-21 school year. All student athletes in grades 7-12 for the 20-21 school term that will be participating in any extra-curricular sport (including cheerleading/dance) are required to have a current KSHSAA physical examination before the first day of practice. The first day of fall practice for 20-21 is August 17, 2020. The physical examination must have been given after May 1, 2020 in order to be valid for the following school year. The appropriate physical forms are linked below and also available at the Troy Central Office (Mon.-Thurs. - 8 a.m. - 4 p.m.) This requirement is a part of our compliance with Kansas State High School Activities Association.

If you have any questions, please contact one of the USD 429 coaches or call the Troy Central Office at 785-985-3950 ext. 2101.

http://www.kshsaa.org/Public/PDF/FORM-PPE.pdf

post_text: As changes are being made, we are very aware that students may be facing some type of struggle or issue in their lives. Whether it be seniors with questions about what is to come, students with preexisting problems, or those with new anxieties about the changes being made, etc., we realize that it is vital we have a school counselor available for those needing support and/or assistance. Our school counselor, Miss Hill, will be available during regular school hours. If your child needs to or would like to speak with the counselor, please send her an email at ehill@troyusd.org, so she can schedule a Zoom meeting with your student.
